[1mNAME[0m
       gozilla - force mozilla to display specified part of a source file.

[1mSYNOPSIS[0m
       [1mgozilla [22m[-b browser][-p][+no] file
       [1mgozilla [22m[-b browser][-p] -d name

[1mDESCRIPTION[0m
       [1mGozilla  [22mforces  [1mmozilla  [22mto  display  specified part of a source file.
       [1mGozilla [22mcan be used with other browsers like firefox and epiphany.

       In advance of  using  this  command,  you  must  execute  [1mgtags[22m(1)  and
       [1mhtags[22m(1)  at the root directory of the project to make tag files.  Then
       you can execute this command anywhere in the project.

       First form:
       You can specify a source file and optional line number.  This syntax is
       similar to [1mvi[22m(1) and [1memacs[22m(1).

       Second form:
       You  can specify a definition name directly. The definition name should
       exist  in  'GTAGS'.  This  option  requires  'HTML/MAP'  generated   by
       [1mhtags[22m(1).

       Some browsers require you to load it before executing [1mgozilla[22m.

